ce:section.ce:para:
Using four brand-new Teflon-lined autoclaves with the same volume (10 mL), 0.1 g yeast extract was dissolved into 6 mL deionized water each. Then four different substances were added into the solution following the sequence below:


Solution-1: 0,1 g ethylenediamine into the solution of yeast extract;



Solution-2: 0.1 g citric acid into the solution of yeast extract;



Solution-3: 0.1 g melamine into the solution of yeast extract;



Solution-4: 0.4 g ammonia water (25%–28%) into the solution of yeast extract.
